 in the primary hand. According to Copeland's Weapon analyzer (only place I have seen this other than people's posts), there is a damage bonus for the primary hand weapon depending on level.<br>
<br>
I am spewing some numbers here, just sort of thinking out loud, to see if my thought process is correct.<br>
<br>
For example:<br>
<br>
Levels 1-30 =  Min Damage of 2<br>
Levels 31-33 = Min Damage of 3<br>
Levels 34-36 = Min Damage of 4<br>
Levels 37-39 = Min Damage of 5<br>
Levels 40-42 = Min Damage of 6<br>
Levels 43-45 = Min Damage of 7<br>
Levels 46-48 = Min Damage of 8<br>
Levels 49-51 = Min Damage of 9<br>
Levels 52-54 = Min Damage of 10<br>
Levels 55-57 = Min Damage of 11<br>
Level     60 = Min Damage of 12<br>
<br>
I want to examine the Wusmslayer, at 25/40 and a Lamentation at 9/18.<br>
<br>
OK What I want to look at is the delay. The first common delay multiplier that these weapons share is at 90 delay. That gives the Wurmy 2 swings and the Lammy 5. <br>
<br>
After 90 delay, and without any damage modifiers, the lammy is doing 45 damage in that 90 delay. <br>
After 90 delay, and without any damage modifiers, the Wurmy is doing 40 damage in that 90 delay. <br>
<br>
Not a big difference there.<br>
<br>
After 90 delay, and With a level 50 damage modifier (Min damge=9), the lammy is doing 90 damage in that 90 delay. <br>
After 90 delay, and With a level 50 damage modifier (Min damge=9), the Wurmy is doing 68 damage in that 90 delay. <br>
<br>
I am not certain if that is even right. At level 50, Copeland's says there is a min 9 damage per swing. *IF* the damage of the sword is added in on top of that, then:<br>
<br>
(Keep in mind 5 swings of a lammy = 2 swings of a wurmy.)<br>
<br>
1 swing  of lammy = 9 dam from weap + 9 dam from level =    18 damage total<br>
2 swings of lammy = 9 dam from weap + 9 dam from level * 2= 36 damage total<br>
3 swings of lammy = 9 dam from weap + 9 dam from level * 3= 54 damage total<br>
4 swings of lammy = 9 dam from weap + 9 dam from level * 4= 72 damage total<br>
5 swings of lammy = 9 dam from weap + 9 dam from level * 5= 90 damage total<br>
<br>
1 swing  of Wurmy = 25 dam from weap + 9 dam from level =    34 damage total<br>
2 swings of Wurmy = 25 dam from weap + 9 dam from level * 2= 68 damage total<br>
<br>
If I'm not a complete and total moron, which I may very well be, that is the reason low delay weapons are preferred over high delay weapons. The minimum damage is raised such that the more swings you get, the more chances you have to do that minimum damage+weapon damage, which means more overall damage in the long haul.<br>
<br>
That would also explain the balance issues the mosscovered twing brought. It would do 108 damage over 90 units of delay at level 50, better than the lammy.<br>
<br>
<br>
